<br>
I said, &quot;Fine, I'll roll on every item then, and we're not restricting by class or who can use it&quot;.<br>
<br>
Although it shocked everyone, we all agreed in the end that if melees could roll on parchments, everyone else should be able to roll on melee gear. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=azuresky>Azuresky</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#333333>(12/6/02 3:36:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1670.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ringofshadows.com/images/Azuresig.jpeg height=168 width=120></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: melees rolling on parchments</span><hr size=1> I am a 61 mage, but my primary character is a 61 warrior. <br>
<br>
The current situation is that my warrior is automatically discounted when folks think about who should get a parchment. <br>
<br>
If I were still 60 or below, I do not think I would have the level of frustration that I do now.  Aye, my magician form is of my secondary character. This does not take away from the fact that my warrior is spending the same amount of time hunting to get other parchments.<br>
<br>
